      "status": "confirmed",
      "summary": "Highly complex CubeSat LoRa gateway payload PCB (395 components, 488 nets) built around a Raspberry Pi Compute Module 5 with Semtech SX1302 gateway baseband, dual SX1250 RF frontends, SX1261 Listen-Before-Talk radio, CMX90A004 2W PA, QPL9095 LNA, SAW filters, 3-way power splitter, dual CAN FD buses, 4 TMP117 temperature sensors, TLA2024 ADC for power monitoring, and elaborate power tree with eFuses, buck converters, and LDOs. The analyzer correctly identified the hierarchical power architecture, voltage dividers, feedback networks, LC/RC filters, I2C bus, reset circuits, LED indicators, protection devices, load switches, and power sequencing. However, it has significant Vref heuristic errors on TPS62912 (used 0.6V instead of 0.8V) and TPS73601 (used 0.6V instead of ~1.204V), the rf_chains and rf_matching sections are empty despite this being an RF-centric design, and CAN FD/SPI/UART buses are undetected.",
